        <speech by="#044d7a53-b109-4393-8fbe-efad8b86a796">
          <from>MS. DIANA WHALEN</from>
          <p>MS. DIANA WHALEN : I think I would be remiss if I didn't say a few words as I know the member has spoken from the heart today and it's really quite moving. We haven't heard much of that in this House in the last number of years, perhaps - number of months, definitely. I want to say that all members of the House have a high respect - certainly we do on this side of the House - have a high respect for the former Minister of Finance. I think he was very well regarded, always, as a member who did his research and who has been here for the right reasons.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
